doc/source/specs/stx-5.0/approved/Manage.message:
Actually, the key object of flock service is the ‘host’, for example sysinv stores all HW resources status with host id; mtce manages host life-cycle;  sw-patch orchestrates patches per host; 

If edgeworker is not landed as ‘host’ object, we need to add another mechanism to inventory their resources, and manage their life-cycle. This is a kind of making another wheel. If so, then why flock services? Since the sysinv and mtce will totally have a different logic path to manage edgeworkers, adding an out-of-band service instead of introducing then to flock service will have the least risk. However, this is not what we intend to. 

What we want is enhancing flock services to extend the core functionality as well as making them more agile by containerization. Maybe after this implementation we could come up with a better mechanism for the sysinv object definition and usage

