I'm fine with this but for the record I would have used such a pattern instead:

    class MyCharm(OSBaseCharm):
        def __init__(self):
            super().register_status_check(self.mycharm_check)

and then the parent `update_status()` will just take care of iterating over the registered functions. This is simpler I think as it doesn't require MyCharm to do some list arithmetic (which could have a bug and damage the original list).

