openstack_dashboard/test/integration_tes.message:
I confirmed this style does not work even in the following simple case.
As a conclusion, I think it is better to prepare a submethod not to call super() multiple times.

  class Foo():
      def __init__(self):
          self.val = self._prepare()

      def _prepare(self):
          return 'x'

  class Bar(Foo):
      def _prepare(self):
          return [
              super()._prepare()
              for i in range(3)
          ]

